      "description": "This 997.2 Carrera S is a pristine example of naturally aspirated precision, featuring the 3.8L DFI flat-six paired with a rare 6-speed manual transaxle. The mechanical integrity is superlative, boasting a clean DME report and a leak-free undercarriage. Equipped with PASM adaptive damping and a factory limited-slip differential, the chassis dynamics remain as sharp as the day it left Stuttgart. Every bushing, synchro, and seals performs within factory tolerances. The exterior features original paint with zero rock chips, while the interior shows no bolster wear or soft-touch plastic degradation. A true collector-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
